data.enText: to be attended by everyone who has the right to attend

data.chText: 新委员会本周举行第一次全会。
data.enText: The new committee holds its first plenary session this week.

data.chText: 理事会拥有全权执行这项协议。
data.enText: The Council has plenary powers to administer the agreement.

example: a plenary session of the legislature

value.def: A plenary session or plenary meeting is one that is attended by everyone who has the right to attend.

example.ex: The programme was approved at a plenary session of the Central Committee last week.
example.tran: 这个方案在上周的中央委员会全体会议上获得了通过。

example.ex: There'll be another plenary at the end of the afternoon after the workshop.
example.tran: 今天下午五六点钟在研讨会结束后还有一次全体会议。
